# RPT report colors (RPT Dashboard overlays)

Use shared theme brushes and styles in `WpfUserControlFramework/PeoplePosTheme.xaml` next to other `Brush.Rpt*` resources. Do not invent new hex values in local `UserControl.Resources` or code-behind for these roles.

## Signed positive / negative text

When a **report overlay** uses **green or red for text** (e.g. positive/negative growth, signed variance, value above/below zero):

| Role | Hex | Theme key |
|------|-----|-----------|
| Positive / favorable | `#22C55E` | `Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground` |
| Negative / unfavorable | `#DC2626` | `Brush.RptReportNegativeForeground` |

### XAML (signed)

- Bind `Foreground` (or `Stroke` on trend icons that pair with that text) with `{StaticResource Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground}` / `{StaticResource Brush.RptReportNegativeForeground}`.

### Code-behind (signed)

- Prefer `Application.Current.TryFindResource("Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground")` (and negative) with a **frozen fallback** `SolidColorBrush` using the same hex values if the app dictionary is not merged yet (see `RptDeliveryVarianceReportOverlay` / `RptTillDrawerVarianceReportOverlay`).

## Approved / Pending status pills

**Client standard:** grey **Approved**, orange/amber **Pending**, label text `#111827` on both. This is the same pair already used on **High-Value Voids** and the non-Critical path on **Low Stock** (`#ECEEF2` for Approved / OK, `#FFFBEB` for Pending / default warning). Do not use the older blue/grey Refunds/Voids inline pair (`#E0E7FF` / `#1E40AF` approved, `#F3F4F6` / `#6B7280` pending).

For operational report rows that bind `StatusVariant` (`Approved` / `Pending`):

| Role | Hex | Theme key |
|------|-----|-----------|
| Approved pill | background `#ECEEF2` (grey), text `#111827` | `Brush.RptReportStatusApprovedBackground` / `Brush.RptReportStatusApprovedForeground` |
| Pending pill | background `#FFFBEB` (orange / amber), text `#111827` | `Brush.RptReportStatusPendingBackground` / `Brush.RptReportStatusPendingForeground` |

Reuse `RptReportApprovedPendingBadgeBorderStyle` and `RptReportApprovedPendingBadgeTextStyle` on the pill `Border` and status `TextBlock` (see `RptHighValueVoidsReportOverlay.xaml`, `RptRefundsReportOverlay.xaml`, `RptVoidsReportOverlay.xaml`).

### XAML (status pills)

- Set the pill `Border` `Style` to `{StaticResource RptReportApprovedPendingBadgeBorderStyle}` and the status `TextBlock` `Style` to `{StaticResource RptReportApprovedPendingBadgeTextStyle}`.

## Out of scope

- Other status semantics (e.g. Low Stock **Critical**) may keep report-local colors until promoted to shared theme keys.
- Non-report UI (Staff, Procurement, Operations) may keep its own palette; this rule targets **RPT Dashboard report overlays** only unless a task explicitly extends it.
